==Offseason==
* December 2, 1958: [[John Herrnstein]] was signed as an amateur free agent by the Phillies.<ref>[http://www.baseball-reference.com/h/herrnjo01.shtml John Herrnstein page at Baseball Reference]</ref>
* December 3, 1958: [[Chuck Essegian]] was traded by the Phillies to the [[St. Louis Cardinals]] for [[Ruben Amaro, Sr.]].<ref>[http://www.baseball-reference.com/a/amaroru01.shtml Ruben Amaro page at Baseball Reference]</ref>
* December 3, 1958: Ruben Gomez was traded by the San Francisco Giants with Valmy Thomas to the Philadelphia Phillies for Jack Sanford. <ref>http://www.baseball-reference.com/g/gomezru01.shtml</ref>
* Prior to 1959 season: [[John Anderson (pitcher)|John Anderson]] was returned by the Phillies to the [[Miami Marlins (IL)|Miami Marlins]] after expiration of minor league working agreement.<ref>[http://www.baseball-reference.com/a/anderjo02.shtml John Anderson page at Baseball Reference]</ref>

==Regular season==
===Season standings===
{{1959 National League Standings}}
===Transactions===
*April 13, 1959: Bobby Del Greco was purchased by the Philadelphia Phillies from the New York Yankees. <ref>http://www.baseball-reference.com/d/delgrbo01.shtml</ref>
*June 5, 1959: Gary Kroll was signed by the Philadelphia Phillies as an amateur free agent. <ref>http://www.baseball-reference.com/k/krollga01.shtml</ref>
*June 6, 1959: Jim Bolger was traded by the Cleveland Indians with cash to the Philadelphia Phillies for Willie Jones. <ref>http://www.baseball-reference.com/b/bolgeji01.shtml</ref>

